1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,336
♪ <i>Oh, Mr. Tailor…</i> ♪

2
00:00:03,420 --> 00:00:07,966
["Mr. Tailor" playing]

3
00:00:08,466 --> 00:00:10,343
- <i>♪ Fix this</i> ♪
- <i>♪ Oh, Mr. Tailor</i> ♪

4
00:00:10,427 --> 00:00:12,679
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

5
00:00:12,762 --> 00:00:16,641
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

6
00:00:16,725 --> 00:00:18,810
[Audrey] <i>So, what's the truth, Dad?</i>

7
00:00:18,893 --> 00:00:20,270
<i>Was I pregnant then?</i>

8
00:00:20,353 --> 00:00:21,730
I'm sorry, child.

9
00:00:21,813 --> 00:00:22,939
We had our reasons.

10
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:23,857
[Audrey] "We"?!

11
00:00:24,691 --> 00:00:25,608
Where is my child?

12
00:00:25,692 --> 00:00:27,444
Where is my child?!

13
00:00:27,527 --> 00:00:29,362
[Dmitri] <i>She's already</i>
<i>looking for her child.</i>

14
00:00:29,446 --> 00:00:31,114
<i>What will I tell her?</i>

15
00:00:31,698 --> 00:00:34,034
Don't mess with me.

16
00:00:34,117 --> 00:00:34,951
[Martina, in English] <i>Of course, Dad.</i>

17
00:00:35,035 --> 00:00:37,412
[Ibyang] I'm going to school?

18
00:00:37,495 --> 00:00:42,041
[in English] Surprise! Welcome
to your student girl era!

19
00:00:42,125 --> 00:00:43,918
You're on another level now, Ibyang!

20
00:00:44,002 --> 00:00:46,254
[Ibyang] <i>They'll just</i>
<i>laugh at me in school.</i>

21
00:00:46,337 --> 00:00:47,255
PREVIOUSLY

22
00:00:47,338 --> 00:00:49,132
[Ibyang] <i>They'll find out that</i>

23
00:00:49,215 --> 00:00:51,718
<i>I don't know how to read or write.</i>

24
00:00:51,801 --> 00:00:54,387
You're a hustler. You can do it!

25
00:00:54,471 --> 00:00:55,638
I believe in you.

26
00:00:55,722 --> 00:00:57,724
[Feliz] <i>Where are Ibyang's parents?</i>

27
00:00:57,807 --> 00:00:59,392
[Ibyang] <i>I don't have parents.</i>

28
00:00:59,476 --> 00:01:01,394
I grew up in an orphanage.

29
00:01:01,478 --> 00:01:02,395
[Feliz] <i>Are they dead?</i>

30
00:01:02,479 --> 00:01:05,148
We'll lose control
when your father gets involved.

31
00:01:05,231 --> 00:01:07,275
We need to find a way,
so they won't find the child.

32
00:01:07,984 --> 00:01:08,860
What's your plan?

33
00:01:08,943 --> 00:01:11,112
She's growing up and ready for school.

34
00:01:11,196 --> 00:01:13,114
She might start looking for her parents.

35
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:15,033
You are her parent now.

36
00:01:15,116 --> 00:01:18,453
With all the good things
you've done for her.

37
00:01:19,162 --> 00:01:21,623
She will never forget that, Atoy.

38
00:01:23,124 --> 00:01:24,918
[music fades]

39
00:01:32,133 --> 00:01:33,134
Oh!

40
00:01:33,718 --> 00:01:34,844
So, Ibyang?

41
00:01:35,720 --> 00:01:36,805
Are you okay now?

42
00:01:38,264 --> 00:01:39,933
- Master…
- [Atoy] Mm?

43
00:01:40,016 --> 00:01:42,393
Can I go to school on another day instead?

44
00:01:42,477 --> 00:01:45,063
- Oh?
- I don't have school supplies

45
00:01:45,146 --> 00:01:46,773
or a uniform yet.

46
00:01:46,856 --> 00:01:49,567
- Ah, really?
- That will make me stand out even more.

47
00:01:49,651 --> 00:01:51,486
- [Atoy] Oh!
- [teasing]

48
00:01:51,569 --> 00:01:52,737
[Tonet] Poor thing.

49
00:01:52,821 --> 00:01:54,989
She says she has none!

50
00:01:55,073 --> 00:01:55,949
Look--

51
00:01:56,032 --> 00:01:58,409
You'll stand out even more

52
00:01:58,493 --> 00:02:01,496
when you have a new bag and lunchbox!

53
00:02:01,579 --> 00:02:05,041
- And socks and shoes!
- [applauds, exclaims]

54
00:02:05,125 --> 00:02:07,669
- Wow!
- And a cute tumbler!

55
00:02:07,752 --> 00:02:09,045
Wow! Tumbler!

56
00:02:09,129 --> 00:02:13,216
And how will you go to school
without a uniform?

57
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:15,927
- [applauds, exclaims]
- Oh? What now? Huh?

58
00:02:16,010 --> 00:02:17,053
Oop!

59
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:18,680
Oh, I thought you didn't want to go?

60
00:02:18,763 --> 00:02:19,806
- [Tonet] Yes, let… let's go.
- Ha?

61
00:02:19,889 --> 00:02:20,723
- I'll take it back, I'll take it back,
- [overlapping chatter]

62
00:02:20,807 --> 00:02:21,975
- take it back!
- Yes, wait a minute.

63
00:02:22,058 --> 00:02:23,518
- Oh…
- Oh, no, no.

64
00:02:23,601 --> 00:02:24,644
I'll go to school!

65
00:02:24,727 --> 00:02:26,563
[pleasant music playing]

66
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:28,106
[Cita] Whoa!

67
00:02:28,189 --> 00:02:29,357
Still don't want to?

68
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:30,733
[Tonet] Mmm…

69
00:02:30,817 --> 00:02:32,777
Wow!

70
00:02:33,361 --> 00:02:35,196
This is nice!

71
00:02:35,989 --> 00:02:38,491
I really feel the school vibe now!

72
00:02:38,575 --> 00:02:40,118
- [Atoy] Oh!
- [Ame giggles]

73
00:02:40,201 --> 00:02:42,245
- Wow.
- Ibyang…

74
00:02:42,954 --> 00:02:45,206
Study hard.

75
00:02:45,290 --> 00:02:46,666
[sentimental music playing]

76
00:02:48,042 --> 00:02:51,170
Yes, master. I'm scared of you.

77
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,548
What… What do you mean…

78
00:02:53,631 --> 00:02:55,300
Psst, psst, hey.

79
00:02:55,383 --> 00:02:56,634
"I'm scared of you"?

80
00:02:56,718 --> 00:03:00,054
Ibyang, you will go to school and study.

81
00:03:00,138 --> 00:03:04,309
And you'll do it not for me, not for us.

82
00:03:04,392 --> 00:03:05,894
But for yourself.

83
00:03:05,977 --> 00:03:08,479
- [Cita] Hmm-mm.
- [Atoy] So, you'll learn something.

84
00:03:08,563 --> 00:03:10,315
But above all, of course,

85
00:03:10,398 --> 00:03:14,193
so you'll be proud of yourself.

86
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:16,821
[Atoy] Hmm?

87
00:03:16,905 --> 00:03:18,531
- [Atoy, in English] Promise?
- [in English] Promise.

88
00:03:19,115 --> 00:03:19,949
Oh.

89
00:03:21,701 --> 00:03:22,744
[Atoy] You'll study?

90
00:03:23,620 --> 00:03:25,914
[chuckles]

91
00:03:25,997 --> 00:03:30,293
[suave theme music playing]

92
00:03:54,525 --> 00:03:55,693
[music fades]

93
00:04:00,990 --> 00:04:02,992
[in English] Ah, Auntie,
your food is here.

94
00:04:03,076 --> 00:04:06,496
[in English] But Grandpa is already
outside with Mom and Dad.

95
00:04:07,413 --> 00:04:08,998
[in English] If…
If you don't want to see them,

96
00:04:09,082 --> 00:04:11,334
I can just tell them
to visit you some other time.

97
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:14,337
Let them in.

98
00:04:16,172 --> 00:04:17,298
Okay, Auntie.

99
00:04:17,382 --> 00:04:18,591
[somber music playing]

100
00:04:37,068 --> 00:04:37,944
[sighs] Audrey.

101
00:04:38,027 --> 00:04:38,987
[in English] No questions, Dad.

102
00:04:42,073 --> 00:04:43,574
[in English] I just want answers.

103
00:04:57,672 --> 00:05:01,301
[in English] You were five months pregnant
when we found out.

104
00:05:04,345 --> 00:05:06,306
Did I give birth to the child?

105
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:10,059
Or did I have a miscarriage?

106
00:05:11,227 --> 00:05:12,478
You went full term.

107
00:05:14,522 --> 00:05:18,526
And gave birth to a baby girl
through C-section.

108
00:05:19,902 --> 00:05:23,197
Audrey, you have to understand,
you were in a coma back then,

109
00:05:23,823 --> 00:05:27,076
and we had no assurance you'd wake up.

110
00:05:28,119 --> 00:05:29,620
That's why I thought

111
00:05:29,704 --> 00:05:32,999
it was best to entrust
the child to someone else.

112
00:05:33,082 --> 00:05:35,293
[pensive music playing]

113
00:05:35,376 --> 00:05:37,837
But I woke up in less than a year.

114
00:05:40,423 --> 00:05:42,842
And years have passed, but…

115
00:05:44,635 --> 00:05:46,387
you never said anything.

116
00:05:46,471 --> 00:05:47,972
[sinister music playing]

117
00:05:48,056 --> 00:05:50,183
[in English] Not even a hint.

118
00:05:52,935 --> 00:05:55,354
- Why?
- [Dmitri] Audrey…

119
00:05:56,898 --> 00:05:59,025
The child would have been a distraction

120
00:05:59,108 --> 00:06:01,152
to your full recovery back then.

121
00:06:01,235 --> 00:06:02,820
And also,

122
00:06:03,571 --> 00:06:05,448
how could you care for the child

123
00:06:05,531 --> 00:06:07,909
if you weren't
fully functional at that time?

124
00:06:10,703 --> 00:06:15,291
We didn't know the circumstances
of your pregnancy,

125
00:06:15,792 --> 00:06:17,627
who the father was.

126
00:06:18,211 --> 00:06:21,547
We decided to hide it from you,

127
00:06:22,423 --> 00:06:24,258
so you could focus on your life.

128
00:06:24,967 --> 00:06:27,512
So, you just decided to abandon my child?

129
00:06:28,805 --> 00:06:31,182
Your grandchild, Dad?

130
00:06:31,265 --> 00:06:33,518
[in English] We thought
it was best for you.

131
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:35,520
[in English] It was
the best decision for you.

132
00:06:35,603 --> 00:06:37,939
We hoped you'd understand us.

133
00:06:38,022 --> 00:06:39,649
- [chuckles sarcastically]
- [music fades]

134
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:41,484
Why should I understand you?!

135
00:06:41,567 --> 00:06:43,653
[unsettling music playing]

136
00:06:43,736 --> 00:06:45,780
You wronged me!

137
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:52,203
You had no right
to deprive me of my child!

138
00:06:52,286 --> 00:06:54,122
This is my body!

139
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:56,082
I was the one pregnant, Dad!

140
00:06:56,165 --> 00:06:58,793
You are not God to take away my child!

141
00:06:58,876 --> 00:07:00,044
My dear, I'm sorry.

142
00:07:00,128 --> 00:07:01,838
- [Audrey sobs]
- [in English] I'm sorry.

143
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:04,132
- [Audrey, in English, softly] Oh, sorry.
- [in English] I'm so sorry!

144
00:07:06,759 --> 00:07:07,885
[in English] Not sorry.

145
00:07:09,303 --> 00:07:11,013
[in English] How could you do this to me?

146
00:07:11,556 --> 00:07:15,560
[in English] I never thought I could
hate you as much as I do right now!

147
00:07:17,019 --> 00:07:20,523
Audrey, don't be angry at Dad.

148
00:07:21,691 --> 00:07:23,484
If you want to be mad,
be mad at me instead.

149
00:07:24,026 --> 00:07:25,611
[in English] I told him to decide.

150
00:07:27,655 --> 00:07:28,948
[in English] I'm sorry.

151
00:07:30,116 --> 00:07:32,660
[Martina, in English] We're…
We're really very sorry, Audrey.

152
00:07:33,703 --> 00:07:35,580
[in English] It was a huge mistake,

153
00:07:35,663 --> 00:07:37,957
and we just want to make it right.

154
00:07:38,624 --> 00:07:40,501
We're already looking for the child.

155
00:07:41,544 --> 00:07:42,837
"Looking"?

156
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:44,046
[music fades]

157
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,756
[Audrey] What do you mean?

158
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:48,134
My child is missing?!

159
00:07:48,217 --> 00:07:49,427
What?!

160
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:51,888
You just gave her away like a cat?!
Is that it?!

161
00:07:52,513 --> 00:07:55,141
[intense music playing]

162
00:08:01,772 --> 00:08:03,149
Audrey…

163
00:08:04,817 --> 00:08:07,737
I brought her to a reputable orphanage.

164
00:08:08,571 --> 00:08:11,365
[in English] But I came across a dilemma.

165
00:08:12,116 --> 00:08:16,204
Unfortunately, that orphanage burned down,

166
00:08:16,287 --> 00:08:21,209
and all records of all children adopted
eight years ago were destroyed.

167
00:08:21,709 --> 00:08:24,420
[pensive music playing]

168
00:08:24,504 --> 00:08:25,505
She's gone?

169
00:08:28,049 --> 00:08:32,929
I might still find her records
at the main office of social services.

170
00:08:33,012 --> 00:08:35,431
But why the orphanage?

171
00:08:36,390 --> 00:08:39,769
Couldn't you have cared
for her yourselves?

172
00:08:40,311 --> 00:08:43,439
It's not like you didn't have money
to pay for a nanny,

173
00:08:43,523 --> 00:08:46,776
but all of you just wanted
to get rid of my baby!

174
00:08:47,443 --> 00:08:48,361
Why?

175
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:51,030
What did the child ever do to you?

176
00:08:51,572 --> 00:08:54,742
We will find your daughter, Audrey.
Okay? I-I-I promise you that.

177
00:08:54,825 --> 00:08:55,952
I'll make it right.

178
00:08:56,035 --> 00:08:57,245
[in English] Bullshit!

179
00:08:57,995 --> 00:09:02,833
If I hadn't found out I was pregnant,
you never would have looked for my child.

180
00:09:03,626 --> 00:09:09,465
[sobs] Not one of you
ever told me the truth!

181
00:09:09,549 --> 00:09:12,343
[rousing music playing]

182
00:09:15,596 --> 00:09:19,141
You are here to study. Not to fight.

183
00:09:19,725 --> 00:09:21,769
If you hear something negative,

184
00:09:21,852 --> 00:09:24,105
whether about yourself

185
00:09:24,188 --> 00:09:26,732
or about others or other things,
what will you do again?

186
00:09:27,233 --> 00:09:29,485
[bustling chatter in the distance]

187
00:09:29,569 --> 00:09:30,903
[gentle music playing]

188
00:09:30,987 --> 00:09:32,905
Thread through the needle.

189
00:09:33,781 --> 00:09:36,659
Pass through, but don't stop.

190
00:09:36,742 --> 00:09:38,035
- [Atoy] Mm-hmm.
- If it gets stuck…

191
00:09:38,786 --> 00:09:39,620
[both snipping]

192
00:09:40,288 --> 00:09:41,330
Scissors.

193
00:09:41,414 --> 00:09:42,623
[Atoy] Okay.

194
00:09:43,916 --> 00:09:45,751
Everything okay now?

195
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:47,420
- Okay.
- Can I go in already?

196
00:09:48,254 --> 00:09:49,922
[Ame] Ah, Ibyang,

197
00:09:50,006 --> 00:09:53,801
you have an extra T-shirt
inside your bag and tissue.

198
00:09:53,884 --> 00:09:56,929
Mmm, and if you need to pee, tell someone.

199
00:09:57,013 --> 00:09:58,639
[Ame] Listen to your teacher.

200
00:09:58,723 --> 00:10:00,725
[Atoy] And say good morning
to your teacher.

201
00:10:00,808 --> 00:10:01,726
[Ibyang] Yes.

202
00:10:01,809 --> 00:10:02,810
- [Ame] Smile!
- Okay?

203
00:10:02,893 --> 00:10:04,520
Be respectful.

204
00:10:04,604 --> 00:10:05,771
- Hmm?
- [Ibyang] Yes.

205
00:10:08,232 --> 00:10:09,483
[Ame] Here's your lunch.

206
00:10:09,567 --> 00:10:10,401
[Tonet] Okay.

207
00:10:10,484 --> 00:10:11,485
[Atoy] Go ahead.

208
00:10:11,569 --> 00:10:12,570
- [Tonet] All right.
- Okay.

209
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:14,363
- Okay.
- [Ame] Listen to your teacher.

210
00:10:14,447 --> 00:10:15,448
[Ibyang] Yes.

211
00:10:16,115 --> 00:10:17,241
[in English] Thank you.

212
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:20,953
I hope I remember everything you said.

213
00:10:21,037 --> 00:10:22,496
[all chuckle]

214
00:10:23,748 --> 00:10:24,957
- Okay.
- Take care, huh?

215
00:10:25,041 --> 00:10:27,418
Oh, your extra T-shirt is inside your bag.

216
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:28,836
- Okay.
- [Atoy] Okay.

217
00:10:29,587 --> 00:10:30,880
[Tonet] Bye!

218
00:10:30,963 --> 00:10:32,840
[Ame] Enjoy, Ibyang!

219
00:10:32,923 --> 00:10:34,717
[music fades]

220
00:10:34,800 --> 00:10:36,135
[Tonet] Answer during recitation!

221
00:10:40,264 --> 00:10:43,601
[gentle music playing]

222
00:10:56,447 --> 00:10:57,531
Let's go.

223
00:11:00,159 --> 00:11:01,369
- Let's go.
- Yeah.

224
00:11:06,916 --> 00:11:08,000
[music fades]

225
00:11:08,084 --> 00:11:09,377
[in English] And you…

226
00:11:10,294 --> 00:11:12,004
[breath quivers] Martina.

227
00:11:13,672 --> 00:11:16,675
You were the one who brought
my child to the orphanage?

228
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:18,677
[unsettling music playing]

229
00:11:18,761 --> 00:11:20,262
You're a woman!

230
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,306
You're a mother too!

231
00:11:22,390 --> 00:11:25,267
And that's what you did
to me and my child?!

232
00:11:27,645 --> 00:11:28,729
Why?

233
00:11:29,438 --> 00:11:31,023
[in English] I'm really sorry, Audrey.

234
00:11:31,107 --> 00:11:32,817
[Audrey sobs]

235
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:34,276
"Sorry"?

236
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:37,655
How dare you say sorry to me!

237
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:41,325
Just admit you wanted to do it!

238
00:11:41,909 --> 00:11:45,413
You hurt me on purpose
because you were jealous!

239
00:11:45,496 --> 00:11:46,372
- [plates shattering]
- Audrey, stop.

240
00:11:46,455 --> 00:11:47,456
Hey, hey, you're going too far.

241
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:48,791
[screaming] That's not enough!

242
00:11:48,874 --> 00:11:52,211
- Auntie, calm down, Auntie.
- What kind of family are you?!

243
00:11:53,629 --> 00:11:55,339
I was right to run away then.

244
00:11:56,382 --> 00:11:58,467
Because you're a worthless family!

245
00:11:58,551 --> 00:11:59,677
You all conspired against me!

246
00:11:59,760 --> 00:12:02,138
You destroyed my and my daughter's life!

247
00:12:02,221 --> 00:12:03,889
[in English] You ruined my life! Get out!

248
00:12:03,973 --> 00:12:05,349
- Calm down, Auntie.
- [in English] Get out!

249
00:12:05,433 --> 00:12:06,267
I'll handle this!

250
00:12:06,350 --> 00:12:08,060
- [in English] Get out!
- You should leave now. Leave now.

251
00:12:08,144 --> 00:12:09,728
[in English] Please, please. Auntie.

252
00:12:09,812 --> 00:12:10,771
[in English] Relax, Auntie.

253
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,274
Okay? Calm down, calm down.

254
00:12:13,357 --> 00:12:16,318
[dramatic music playing]

255
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,987
[sobs]

256
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:19,822
Where is my daughter? [softly]

257
00:12:20,614 --> 00:12:23,117
[sobs] Gavin, where is my child?

258
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:26,328
Calm down, Auntie. Calm down.

259
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:28,664
What happened to her?

260
00:12:33,210 --> 00:12:36,046
[sobbing]

261
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:46,807
[in English] Class, let's all welcome
your new classmate, Ivy Santos!

262
00:12:49,143 --> 00:12:51,145
Introduce yourself to them.

263
00:12:51,228 --> 00:12:52,813
[in English] Tell us something
about yourself.

264
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:53,981
Don't be shy.

265
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:56,525
Hello!

266
00:12:57,526 --> 00:12:59,820
[in English] My name is Ivy Santos.

267
00:13:00,613 --> 00:13:01,822
Just call me Ibyang.

268
00:13:02,990 --> 00:13:05,367
Class, you can ask Ibyang questions.

269
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:06,911
Yes, Thalia?

270
00:13:06,994 --> 00:13:09,288
Ibyang, why are you only here now?

271
00:13:10,206 --> 00:13:12,166
Um…

272
00:13:12,249 --> 00:13:15,002
[sneaky music playing]

273
00:13:15,085 --> 00:13:16,754
We just moved here.

274
00:13:16,837 --> 00:13:18,547
I came from somewhere far.

275
00:13:19,673 --> 00:13:20,549
[in English] Yes, Jessie?

276
00:13:21,050 --> 00:13:22,843
[in English] What's your favorite color?

277
00:13:23,552 --> 00:13:25,471
[Ibyang, in English] Pink and purple.

278
00:13:26,639 --> 00:13:27,973
[teacher] Grey?

279
00:13:28,057 --> 00:13:30,267
What are your parents' names?

280
00:13:30,351 --> 00:13:32,269
Where do they work?

281
00:13:32,353 --> 00:13:35,439
[music fades]

282
00:13:38,943 --> 00:13:41,529
[quirky music playing]

283
00:13:41,612 --> 00:13:42,988
Hey! There's a rat!

284
00:13:43,072 --> 00:13:44,198
There's a rat! There, oh!

285
00:13:44,281 --> 00:13:46,534
[screaming, panicking]

286
00:13:49,245 --> 00:13:50,704
[all screaming, panicking]

287
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:52,748
There! Look! A rat!

288
00:13:52,831 --> 00:13:54,625
There it is!

289
00:13:55,459 --> 00:13:56,460
There, oh!

290
00:13:57,211 --> 00:13:58,379
[sighs]

291
00:14:01,006 --> 00:14:01,924
Dad.

292
00:14:06,303 --> 00:14:07,721
Uh, Dad, don't worry anymore.

293
00:14:08,931 --> 00:14:11,433
I'm finding a way to find the child,

294
00:14:11,517 --> 00:14:12,851
so everything will be okay.

295
00:14:15,145 --> 00:14:16,105
[groans]

296
00:14:16,188 --> 00:14:17,565
- [Dmitri] What now?
- [Martina] Red, Red, Red!

297
00:14:17,648 --> 00:14:18,983
Are you going to fight back?!

298
00:14:19,066 --> 00:14:20,734
- Go ahead, fight!
- [Martina] Dad!

299
00:14:20,818 --> 00:14:22,403
- Fight!
- [Martina] Dad, please! Please, please!

300
00:14:22,486 --> 00:14:23,821
[in English] Calm down, Dad! Please!

301
00:14:23,904 --> 00:14:26,073
You think everything will be okay,

302
00:14:26,156 --> 00:14:27,825
even if the child is found?!

303
00:14:27,908 --> 00:14:29,994
- [in English] This is all your fault!
- I know, I know!

304
00:14:30,077 --> 00:14:31,704
That's why I'm trying to fix it, right?!

305
00:14:31,787 --> 00:14:33,080
What do you want?
You want me to do nothing?

306
00:14:33,163 --> 00:14:34,540
That's why I'm fixing it!

307
00:14:34,623 --> 00:14:36,333
[in English] Why did I
even listen to you?!

308
00:14:36,834 --> 00:14:39,920
You've never done anything right ever.

309
00:14:40,004 --> 00:14:41,380
You're always a failure!

310
00:14:41,463 --> 00:14:43,924
That's why I won't rely on you anymore!

311
00:14:44,008 --> 00:14:45,634
Why does it seem like I never do
anything right in your eyes, huh?!

312
00:14:45,718 --> 00:14:47,595
You always see me as a failure!

313
00:14:47,678 --> 00:14:49,430
[in English] You really want to know why?!

314
00:14:49,513 --> 00:14:50,890
[tense music playing]

315
00:14:50,973 --> 00:14:54,059
I lost your mother because of you.

316
00:14:54,143 --> 00:14:58,022
Maybe I'll lose my child
because of you too!

317
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:00,858
I'm your child too!

318
00:15:02,026 --> 00:15:03,027
Did you forget?!

319
00:15:03,110 --> 00:15:04,111
- Hon, Hon!
- Ha?!

320
00:15:04,194 --> 00:15:05,946
Find the child.

321
00:15:06,030 --> 00:15:07,489
Find the child!

322
00:15:09,783 --> 00:15:11,660
[music fades]

323
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:13,412
[smirks]

324
00:15:13,495 --> 00:15:16,707
[sinister music playing]

325
00:15:16,790 --> 00:15:18,083
[sighs]

326
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:20,377
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

327
00:15:20,461 --> 00:15:24,381
[in English] Hon, don't think about Dad
right now, okay?

328
00:15:24,965 --> 00:15:27,551
[in English] He's just really,
really stressed out right now, okay?

329
00:15:28,135 --> 00:15:29,011
[in English] Look at me.

330
00:15:30,095 --> 00:15:31,013
Hon.

331
00:15:31,972 --> 00:15:34,099
He's been stressed my whole life,
hasn't he?!

332
00:15:36,018 --> 00:15:38,479
[music swells]

333
00:15:48,322 --> 00:15:51,367
I'll bring that later to Ibyang's school.

334
00:15:53,786 --> 00:15:55,621
[Atoy] Norma Cruz.

335
00:15:57,998 --> 00:15:59,375
She was the one who found her?

336
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:03,545
She was the former directress
at Tahanan ng Bukas.

337
00:16:03,629 --> 00:16:06,048
Her name is listed as the finder

338
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,466
when a child is left in her care

339
00:16:08,133 --> 00:16:11,720
or when a child
is left at the orphanage gate.

340
00:16:11,804 --> 00:16:14,932
She was also the one who gave
the name Ivy Santos to Ibyang.

341
00:16:16,725 --> 00:16:18,060
There's an address here.

342
00:16:18,143 --> 00:16:19,395
I'll just go there.

343
00:16:19,979 --> 00:16:22,356
Atoy, she doesn't live there anymore.

344
00:16:22,439 --> 00:16:23,565
She's a nun.

345
00:16:25,651 --> 00:16:27,611
Do you know which congregation
she belongs to?

346
00:16:28,362 --> 00:16:30,698
I'll ask my former colleague.

347
00:16:32,116 --> 00:16:33,283
[clears throat]

348
00:16:33,367 --> 00:16:34,702
[gentle music playing]

349
00:16:34,785 --> 00:16:36,370
Uh, Atoy…

350
00:16:36,453 --> 00:16:39,748
Do you want to find Ibyang's parents,

351
00:16:39,832 --> 00:16:44,128
so the responsibility of caring

352
00:16:44,211 --> 00:16:45,879
and schooling falls on them?

353
00:16:45,963 --> 00:16:47,339
Not really.

354
00:16:48,132 --> 00:16:49,883
But if they can, why not?

355
00:16:50,718 --> 00:16:54,096
Whatever happens, I won't abandon Ibyang.

356
00:16:54,179 --> 00:16:58,350
What I want is for her
to know her parents.

357
00:16:58,434 --> 00:17:00,477
So she knows where she came from, right?

358
00:17:00,561 --> 00:17:02,229
[gentle music playing]

359
00:17:02,312 --> 00:17:05,024
What if they don't want to know Ibyang?

360
00:17:05,941 --> 00:17:08,861
Then… Then no, I won't force it.

361
00:17:08,944 --> 00:17:10,988
[smirks] As for me…

362
00:17:11,071 --> 00:17:13,866
I'll do everything so that one day,

363
00:17:13,949 --> 00:17:15,826
they'll be proud of Ibyang.

364
00:17:17,369 --> 00:17:19,163
[sentimental music playing]

365
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:24,793
Ah, ma'am, we don't have
any records of a child brought here

366
00:17:24,877 --> 00:17:28,380
to Tahanan ng Bukas in March 2018.

367
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:31,800
Based on our database,
we don't have a record from that time.

368
00:17:31,884 --> 00:17:33,677
[pensive music playing]

369
00:17:33,761 --> 00:17:35,095
What do we do now?

370
00:17:35,846 --> 00:17:37,723
How will we search for the child
you gave up for adoption?

371
00:17:37,806 --> 00:17:39,892
Uh, what was her name?

372
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,604
[stammers, in English] I don't know.
I wasn't the one who named her.

373
00:17:43,687 --> 00:17:46,899
What I remember is the directress
of the orphanage at that time.

374
00:17:47,441 --> 00:17:48,567
[in English] I'm sure she would know.

375
00:17:48,650 --> 00:17:53,405
Um, maybe you can tell me
who the directress was in 2018?

376
00:17:54,073 --> 00:17:55,532
[laptop keys clicking]

377
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:57,993
Unbelievable. You don't
even remember her name?

378
00:17:58,077 --> 00:17:59,703
[sinister music playing]

379
00:17:59,787 --> 00:18:00,746
[Martina] How would I know?

380
00:18:00,829 --> 00:18:03,165
[in English] I didn't have
to know her at the time, Red!

381
00:18:03,248 --> 00:18:05,417
How was I supposed to know
we'd be looking for her again now?

382
00:18:05,501 --> 00:18:08,504
[laptop keys clicking]

383
00:18:09,505 --> 00:18:11,924
Ms. Norma Cruz, based on the record.

384
00:18:12,007 --> 00:18:13,300
Is this her?

385
00:18:13,842 --> 00:18:15,094
[Martina, in English] Uh, yes, that's her.

386
00:18:15,177 --> 00:18:16,553
[in English] That-That's her!

387
00:18:16,637 --> 00:18:21,600
Um… maybe you have some information
you can give us about her.

388
00:18:21,683 --> 00:18:23,560
Uh, ma'am, that's difficult.

389
00:18:23,644 --> 00:18:25,729
Because their official records
were already burned.

390
00:18:30,818 --> 00:18:33,862
[in English] Maybe this will
motivate you to help us find her?

391
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:38,492
All right, ma'am.

392
00:18:38,575 --> 00:18:40,035
We'll just call you.

393
00:18:44,957 --> 00:18:46,125
[sniffs]

394
00:18:47,292 --> 00:18:49,294
[music fades]

395
00:18:53,590 --> 00:18:56,635
[pensive music playing]

396
00:18:58,679 --> 00:19:00,639
Hi, Ibyang!

397
00:19:00,722 --> 00:19:02,266
Do you still remember me?

398
00:19:02,850 --> 00:19:04,768
Of course.

399
00:19:04,852 --> 00:19:06,854
Ah, I'm Janine.

400
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:08,981
How old are you?

401
00:19:09,064 --> 00:19:10,566
Eight years old.

402
00:19:12,359 --> 00:19:14,278
Why are you still in grade 1?

403
00:19:14,361 --> 00:19:16,572
You should be in grade 2, Ibyang.

404
00:19:18,073 --> 00:19:20,242
Maybe you're dumb,
that's why they put you there.

405
00:19:20,742 --> 00:19:21,660
[cackles]

406
00:19:26,081 --> 00:19:28,876
[music fades]

407
00:19:28,959 --> 00:19:30,669
[Atoy] <i>You are here to study.</i>

408
00:19:30,752 --> 00:19:32,880
Not to fight.

409
00:19:32,963 --> 00:19:34,923
If you hear something negative,

410
00:19:35,007 --> 00:19:37,092
whether about yourself

411
00:19:37,176 --> 00:19:39,553
or about others or other things,
what will you do again?

412
00:19:39,636 --> 00:19:41,346
[pensive music playing]

413
00:19:41,430 --> 00:19:44,099
Thread and needle, cut.

414
00:19:44,183 --> 00:19:47,352
Thread and needle, cut.

415
00:19:47,436 --> 00:19:51,023
Thread and needle, scissors.

416
00:19:51,106 --> 00:19:52,274
What's that?

417
00:19:52,357 --> 00:19:55,444
[whispering indistinctly]

418
00:19:56,236 --> 00:19:57,613
[sighs]

419
00:20:16,048 --> 00:20:18,008
[music fades]

420
00:20:22,679 --> 00:20:25,599
[sneaky music playing]

421
00:20:34,566 --> 00:20:36,235
Ibyang!

422
00:20:36,318 --> 00:20:38,695
Your cheap tumbler, you left it.

423
00:20:54,711 --> 00:20:57,256
[music fades]

424
00:21:00,425 --> 00:21:04,304
[gentle music playing]

425
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:16,275
[Mother Superior] Sister Norma
is not allowed to talk

426
00:21:16,358 --> 00:21:20,362
or entertain visitors, not even
her relatives or the police.

427
00:21:20,445 --> 00:21:22,114
[in English] She's very busy.

428
00:21:23,407 --> 00:21:27,202
Uh, what is she busy with, if I may ask?

429
00:21:27,869 --> 00:21:31,540
She just began
her one-year vow of silence.

430
00:21:32,249 --> 00:21:36,003
[in English] A one-year vow
of silence for spiritual focus.

431
00:21:36,503 --> 00:21:40,257
She's also abstaining from eating meat so…

432
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:42,134
come back next year.

433
00:21:42,926 --> 00:21:45,971
Next year. Wow. Seriously? Next year?

434
00:21:46,054 --> 00:21:48,098
[suave music playing]

435
00:21:48,181 --> 00:21:53,145
Son, we're not close enough
for me to joke with you.

436
00:21:53,228 --> 00:21:54,521
[Atoy inhales]

437
00:21:54,604 --> 00:21:56,106
[in English] God bless you.

438
00:21:58,692 --> 00:21:59,735
[in English] Sorry.

439
00:22:04,906 --> 00:22:05,866
[clears throat]

440
00:22:09,870 --> 00:22:13,248
Uh, Auntie, I'll just drop by the school
and my friend's house.

441
00:22:13,832 --> 00:22:16,209
But Manang is already
on the way to accompany you.

442
00:22:17,169 --> 00:22:18,420
Thank you, Gavin.

443
00:22:20,005 --> 00:22:22,966
[in English] I'm really sorry
that you had to see that.

444
00:22:23,675 --> 00:22:26,720
Auntie, I understand why you're angry.

445
00:22:26,803 --> 00:22:28,388
Especially at my parents.

446
00:22:28,972 --> 00:22:32,017
But I'm just worried that you
might only focus on the anger.

447
00:22:32,976 --> 00:22:34,102
[in English] What do you mean?

448
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:37,272
[in English] I mean,
not to dismiss what they did.

449
00:22:37,981 --> 00:22:40,400
But it's nice to know
that you have a child, right?

450
00:22:40,984 --> 00:22:44,404
- [pensive music playing]
- [chuckles softly]

451
00:22:44,988 --> 00:22:46,698
Who does she look like?

452
00:22:47,199 --> 00:22:48,825
You or the father?

453
00:22:50,702 --> 00:22:52,954
Is the mystery guy
from the island the father?

454
00:22:56,792 --> 00:22:58,293
He is.

455
00:22:58,376 --> 00:22:59,461
Oh.

456
00:23:00,504 --> 00:23:01,922
Does he know you have a child?

457
00:23:04,132 --> 00:23:05,050
[in English] Who knows?

458
00:23:05,133 --> 00:23:06,927
Maybe he even has your daughter.

459
00:23:07,010 --> 00:23:09,262
[gentle music playing]

460
00:23:09,930 --> 00:23:11,431
[in English] Anyway, Auntie, I have to go.

461
00:23:11,515 --> 00:23:13,183
[in English] Just message me
if you need anything. Okay?

462
00:23:13,266 --> 00:23:15,894
- [in English] Yes.
- [in English] Rest well, Auntie. Okay?

463
00:23:15,977 --> 00:23:17,145
[in English] Bye-bye!

464
00:23:23,068 --> 00:23:24,319
[door clicks shut]

465
00:23:44,339 --> 00:23:46,049
[line rings]

466
00:23:46,133 --> 00:23:47,259
[Mercado] <i>Ms. Regalia!</i>

467
00:23:48,051 --> 00:23:51,513
Before anything else,
I want to apologize for the inconvenience.

468
00:23:51,596 --> 00:23:53,598
[in English] But unfortunately,

469
00:23:53,682 --> 00:23:57,811
The Master Cutter's services
are no longer available to you.

470
00:23:58,395 --> 00:23:59,938
[in English] I'm not after that.

471
00:24:01,148 --> 00:24:05,026
I just want to get his personal number.

472
00:24:05,527 --> 00:24:08,238
[scoffs, in English]
Classified information.

473
00:24:08,989 --> 00:24:11,867
I'm sure your father already told you that

474
00:24:11,950 --> 00:24:14,202
we will no longer transact with you.

475
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:15,162
[scoffs]

476
00:24:15,245 --> 00:24:16,454
[in English] Nothing personal.

477
00:24:16,538 --> 00:24:19,541
[tense music playing]

478
00:24:19,624 --> 00:24:22,544
Thank you, and good day, Ms. Regalia!

479
00:24:28,049 --> 00:24:31,261
[electronic blipping]

480
00:24:33,054 --> 00:24:36,057
[tense music playing]

481
00:24:38,602 --> 00:24:42,272
The social worker just told me
that Norma Cruz is housed in a convent.

482
00:24:42,355 --> 00:24:43,190
What is she doing there?

483
00:24:43,273 --> 00:24:44,232
[Martina] <i>She's already a nun.</i>

484
00:24:44,316 --> 00:24:45,942
- Sister Norma, Sister Norma!
- [in English] Excuse me?!

485
00:24:46,026 --> 00:24:47,527
- [Red, in English] Uh… Wait.
- [Martina, in English] Excuse me!

486
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:51,489
Eight years ago, my wife handed you
a two-month-old baby.

487
00:24:51,573 --> 00:24:54,576
I'll enter the convent,
so I can talk to Sister Norma.

488
00:24:54,659 --> 00:24:57,579
[Atoy] <i>She's the only one who knows</i>
<i>where Ibyang really came from.</i>

489
00:24:58,163 --> 00:25:02,292
Ah, Sister, Sister Norma's quarters
are still being prepared.

490
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:04,044
<i>Just bring that to the Rose Garden.</i>

491
00:25:04,127 --> 00:25:04,961
UP NEXT

492
00:25:05,045 --> 00:25:06,087
[nun] Sister…

493
00:25:06,796 --> 00:25:09,549
Why are you the one
bringing food to Sister Norma?

494
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:12,010
♪ <i>Holding the scissors</i> ♪

495
00:25:12,093 --> 00:25:15,305
♪ <i>One cut, and it's settled</i> ♪

496
00:25:15,388 --> 00:25:17,474
Subtitle translation by: Rachel C. Arias
